{
  "id": "phekb-fibromyalgia-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "fibromyalgia",
  "name": "Fibromyalgia - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying fibromyalgia patients via Condition + MedicationRequest. Path C (med only without dx) is large because the meds are also used for depression, neuropathic pain, migraine, insomnia.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete fibromyalgia patient population. Some patients have a coded fibromyalgia diagnosis. Others are on duloxetine, gabapentin, or amitriptyline for chronic pain or related conditions without a formal fibromyalgia diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and chronic pain medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all fibromyalgia patients.",
    "broad": "Find all fibromyalgia patients — by diagnosis or by chronic-pain medications (duloxetine, gabapentin, amitriptyline). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all fibromyalgia patients using a union across Condition and MedicationRequest resources. Search Condition resources for fibromyalgia — coded in SNOMED CT as fibromyositis, the canonical concept — and separately search MedicationRequest resources for the agents commonly used to manage fibromyalgia symptoms: duloxetine, gabapentin, and amitriptyline, each coded in RxNorm. Union the patient sets; the medication path captures treated patients who may lack a formal diagnosis, but these drugs carry heavy cross-indication — duloxetine for depression and anxiety, gabapentin for epilepsy and neuropathic pain, amitriptyline for depression and migraine prophylaxis — so the medication-only cohort will include many non-fibromyalgia patients."
  },
